 L_{\lambda} = \frac{2c^{2}h}{\lambda^{5}\left( \exp\left( \frac{hc}{\lambda kT} \right)-1 \right)}
 L_{\lambda} = \int_{0}^{\inf} \frac{2c^{2}h}{\lambda^{5}\left( \exp\left( \frac{hc}{\lambda kT} \right)-1 \right)} d\lambda
a=\dfrac{hc}{kT}
t=a/\lambda \Rightarrow d\lambda=-a\,dt/t^2
\displaystyle \frac{1}{1-e^{-t}}=\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} e^{-kt}
(k+1)t=x
I=\int_0^{\infty} \frac{d\lambda}{\lambda^5 \left(\exp\left(\frac{a}{\lambda}\right)-1\right)}
I=\frac{1}{a^4}\int_0^{\infty} \frac{t^3}{e^t-1}\,dt=\frac{1}{a^4}\int_0^{\infty} \frac{t^3e^{-t}}{1-e^{-t}}\,dt
I=\frac{1}{a^4}\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \int_0^{\infty} t^3e^{-(k+1)t}\,dt
\Rightarrow I=\frac{1}{a^4}\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{1}{(k+1)^4}\int_0^{\infty}x^3e^{-x}=\frac{1}{a^4}\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{1}{(k+1)^4}\Gamma(4)=\frac{3!}{a^4}\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{1}{(k+1)^4}
\Rightarrow I=\frac{6}{a^4}\sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \frac{1}{k^4}\frac{6}{a^4}\frac{\pi^4}{90}=\frac{\pi^4}{15a^4}
2hc^2I=2hc^2\frac{\pi^4}{15}\frac{k^4T^4}{h^4c^4}=\boxed{\dfrac{2\pi^4k^4}{15h^3c^2}T^4}
